<paragraph blockId="3.[317,1271,852,1795]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
– Described from the 
<collectingRegion box="[1180,1269,1025,1046]" country="Russia" name="Primorskiy" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Maritime</collectingRegion>
Territory (Spassk) of Asiatic 
<collectingCountry box="[600,664,1054,1075]" name="Russia" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="BELOKOBYLSKIJ, S. A." box="[678,937,1054,1075]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="163 - 298" refId="ref22378" refString="BELOKOBYLSKIJ, S. A. (1998) Tribe Alysiini. In: Key to the Insects of Russian Far East. Vol. IV. Neuropteroidea, Mecoptera, Hymenoptera, Pt. 3: 163 - 298. [In Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1998">BELOKOBYLSKIJ 1998: 274</bibRefCitation>
) on the basis of 
<specimenCount box="[1098,1205,1054,1075]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="female">two female</specimenCount>
specimens. New to the fauna of 
<collectingCountry box="[575,637,1083,1104]" name="South Korea" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Korea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[317,1271,852,1795]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
– The single Korean female deviates in five features from the description: (1) antenna with 22 antennomeres (26–27); (2) ovipositor sheath one-fifth as long as fore wing; (3) medio-longitudinal sulcus ending at declivous part of mesoscutum; (4) head and mesosoma black, first tergite rusty, metasoma brownish black, legs yellow; (5) body 
<quantity box="[1043,1099,1169,1190]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
